And so Paul concludes, God loves us and we don't deserve it.

25:28.861 --> 25:38.130
And if God loved us when we don't deserve it, sending his son to die for enemies of God, how much more sure and certain can we be without a shadow of a doubt,

25:38.658 --> 25:48.330
that we will be so utterly saved by his life, meaning as Christ has been raised again from the dead, how surely do you live with him and in him?

25:48.410 --> 25:54.698
It's through Jesus that we've been granted true and real peace.

25:55.880 --> 26:06.633
Peace before our Father and Heaven not receiving just wrath and condemnation for our sins, but being welcomed as sons and daughters of God.

26:06.713 --> 26:07.314
Peace.

26:07.554 --> 26:16.183
in this life we live right now in a peace that we can take to the bank and we can rest upon us, surely.

26:19.807 --> 26:37.266
Now, what I want you to see from this passage is that, again, simply put, through Jesus Christ and the peace He brings to bear in us, we know Jesus, who is our wonderful counselor, our mighty God,

26:37.858 --> 26:43.406
our everlasting Father and we can rejoice that He is indeed our Prince of Peace.

26:45.049 --> 26:52.380
We know the glorious benefits of these aspects because through Christ there is peace between God and man.

26:52.400 --> 26:54.703
I want you to think about this.

26:54.804 --> 27:01.534
What is it that the angelic host sings and announces at the birth of Jesus?

27:03.317 --> 27:06.962
Luke records that and suddenly there was with

27:07.138 --> 27:21.935
the angel, a multitude of the heavenly hosts, praising God, saying, Glory to God in the highest and on earth peace among those with whom he is well pleased.

27:23.316 --> 27:28.842
How on earth can God be pleased with you and with me?

27:28.882 --> 27:35.730
In what world can God look upon sinners like me and say, I am pleased with Zach?

27:37.506 --> 27:48.637
Well, surely this love, this pleasing that God looks upon me is not in Zach, but it's in his son.

27:48.677 --> 27:51.459
It's because there has been peace brought.

27:51.499 --> 28:06.834
This is not the absence of war or the presence of tranquility, but peace brought about and bought by the blood of Christ, the one who came to live and to die and to be raised again, that we might have life forever.

28:07.010 --> 28:11.036
with and in and before God forever.

28:13.240 --> 28:13.881
Let's pray together.

28:13.901 --> 28:16.805
Would you pray with me?

28:16.825 --> 28:22.914
Father, we thank you for in your eternal counsel, O Lord.

28:24.056 --> 28:27.541
You saw fit to make a way that we may return.

28:29.504 --> 28:33.170
O Lord, when we were by nature children,

28:33.698 --> 28:34.299
of wrath.

28:34.319 --> 28:35.840
We were at enmity with you.

28:35.860 --> 28:39.144
We were rebels clamoring for your throne.

28:39.164 --> 28:42.567
And yet you saved us and redeemed us.

28:44.309 --> 28:49.794
And Father, we thank you that you have given us every reason that we might gather here on your day to praise your glorious name.

28:51.236 --> 29:01.426
Father, we pray that you would hide these truths in our heart, that you would have us wonder and marvel at grace for those hours, love that is ours, that we might be welcomed into your presence through Jesus.

29:02.370 --> 29:08.884
And so God, we ask that you would fill us with all joy, with all praise, with all submission, with all humility.

29:09.946 --> 29:12.432
Father, we might seek to love you and know you.

29:12.452 --> 29:13.735
We pray this in Jesus' name.

29:14.336 --> 29:15.378
Amen.

